eu.webtoolkit.jwt.WTreeView.getColumnFormat(int)
          use WTreeView.getItemDelegateForColumn(int column) to customize the formatting. This method will try to cast the WTreeView.getItemDelegateForColumn(int column) to a WItemDelegate and return the format. 
eu.webtoolkit.jwt.WKeyEvent.getKeyCode()
          The value returned is somewhat browser-specific, and it is therefore recommended to use the WKeyEvent.getKey() method instead. 
eu.webtoolkit.jwt.WEnvironment.getPathInfo()
          Use WEnvironment.getInternalPath() instead, which is consistent with the internal paths generated by Wt.This is the equivalent of the CGI PATH_INFO environment variable.

Assume for example that the application was deployed at "stuff/app.wt". When the user accesses the application using the URL "http://www.mydomain.com/stuff/app.wt" , this method would return an empty string ( ""). When the user accesses the site using "http://www.mydomain.com/stuff/app.wt/this/there" , the result would be "/this/there".

Together with WEnvironment.getParameter(String name), this allows you to supply the application with initial information.
